	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>There is 1 special ability that you should consider... TELEPORTATION.&nbsp;&nbsp;We are one of only 2 classes that can do this and we are the only class that can go to the planes.  This may not seem like such a big deal, but have you ever stuck with a wizard till lvl 29 or higher?  You can make more cash than ANYONE (Including Enchanter Jewelers) if you know what you are doing.  Think about this:<br><br>You work for an enchanter jeweler teleporting yourself all over the world and selling stuff to people in various zones.  Then for your services you get some of the profit that is earned.  An enchie is constantly stuck in such places as east commons tunnel selling their wares because they do not want to walk.  This means that to sell their stuff PEOPLE HAVE TO COME TO THEM.  You on the other hand are able to teleport all over the place and go to the buyers.  This type of work can be started at lvl 24 when you have a total of 8 personal gates that you can use.<br><br>Think about this as well:<br><br>Your group teleport powers are a never ending source of cash as well.  I normally see a teleport done for 10pp a person and sometimes as much as 50pp a person.  Considering the fact that a teleport takes only a few seconds to do and is constantly needed by all classes except druids, you can see how the money can build up fast.<br><br>What good is all this cash?  You can buy high power items for your wizard.  Then once your wizard is properly outfitted with the most powerful items that can be bought.  This means that you will advance much faster to higher levels because your int is much higher and your defenses are stronger.<br><br>Do not abandon your wizard.  Not having a pet is not the end of the world.  I have discovered (and told in another post here) about the error of thinking in wizard setups.  Put 2 serpentine bracers on your wizard to start with and perhaps a pair of SilverSilk Leggings... Watch what happens when you try to solo.  Suddenly things become easier to do and some "special" areas of intrest pop up.  Things that have not been considered before.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
